This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with the task of human pose estimation using convolutional neural networks. The use of intermediate supervision and bottom-up, top-down processing also suggests that it may belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of pooling and upsampling techniques may suggest that it belongs to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the use of benchmarks to evaluate the performance of the proposed method may suggest that it belongs to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
